This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of facial affect estimation using neural networks. The use of deep residual and convolutional networks also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of multimedia data, specifically facial images, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The task of affective computing also involves human-computer interaction, which could place it in the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for affective computing could also place it in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
